Citations
Date:  0/0/1951
Source:  NZ High Country
Author:  MCLEOD
Vol / Page:  23
Edition:
Quote:  Someone asked me the other day what I meant by a bluff. To us a bluff is any precipitous outcrop of rock or any steep broken face where the rock is bare and the fragments fall away below in scree and shingle slide.
